Introduction

F.able, formerly known as ENERFIVE, is a South Korean K-Pop boy group under Haeirum Entertainment that consists of three members: Sihoon, Jeong, and Hojun. The group was originally set to debut on May 28th, 2020, but was postponed due to unavoidable circumstances. F.able officially debuted on June 5th, 2020, with the digital single "Burn It Up" featuring two new members, Junhyoung and Jaehyun after the departure of Doha and Youngwon in 2020.

Originally, F.able was a seven-member band until members Doha and Youngwon both left the group on August 24th, 2020.

It is presumed that F.able has disbanded due to 3 members being revealed to be part of a new upcoming group, Enphaze. Sihoon, Junhyeong and Jeon were revealed on March 22, 2024.
